cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.CV, cs.ET, cs.LG 

The paper presents a biorealistic model for early vision processing by incorporating memristive nanodevices. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Emerging Technologies (cs.ET), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Learning (cs.LG), and possibly Robotics (cs.RO) as well. However, since the focus of the paper is on the use of memristive devices for neuromorphic architectures, we can assume that cs.NE and cs.ET are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.RO.
